               <msContents class="#CM">
                  <summary><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">A catalogue of the Tamil manuscripts in the now BnF by Léon Feer, according to the title on the spine.</p>
<p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">The codex contains:
<list rend="numbered">
  <item>A list of 63 manuscripts (Tamil, Sanskrit, Telugu, Kannada) sent by the Jesuits of Pondicherry (<locus facs="7">U1</locus>).</item>
  <item>An alphabetical list of the Tamil works in the BnF manuscripts: title in Tamil transcription, title in Roman transliteration, translation in French (in red ink), and shelfmark (<locus facs="15">U2</locus>).</item>
  </list>
</p>
<p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Composite manuscript described as a multi-text manuscript for the sake of convenience.</p>
<p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Description based on the digital images available on Gallica.</p>
   <p>Dimensions after Cabaton (1912).</p>      </summary>
                  
